                                    <div class="faq-section" style="margin-top: 40px;">
                                        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
                                        <h3>Are Kolkata-based studios reliable for international clients?</h3>
                                        <p>Top-tier Kolkata studios deliver to US, UK, UAE and Australian clients with the same SLA as Bangalore peers. The stereotype that Kolkata is 'slow' is two decades out of date — Sector V and New Town firms now run 24/7 ops with daily standups overlapping US PT and EST hours.</p>
                                        <h3>How do Kolkata rates compare to offshoring further (Vietnam / Philippines)?</h3>
                                        <p>Kolkata is roughly 10–20% more expensive than Vietnam, but with stronger English, Indian regulatory familiarity (GST, DPDP, RBI), and better React Native / Flutter / AI talent depth. For Indian-market apps Kolkata wins on TCO; for purely English-language Western apps, Vietnam / Philippines can be cheaper.</p>
                                        <h3>Can a Kolkata studio handle Apple / Google store deployment?</h3>
                                        <p>Yes. Most established studios publish under the client's own Apple Developer ($99/yr) and Google Play Console ($25 one-time) accounts. Insist on this — agencies that insist on publishing under their own account risk holding your app hostage.</p>
                                        <h3>What's the typical engagement model?</h3>
                                        <p>Fixed-scope for the first MVP (clear milestone payments), then T&amp;M or dedicated team for ongoing work. A senior dev costs &#8377;1.6L–&#8377;2.6L/month dedicated; a 4-person pod with PM + senior + 2 mid runs &#8377;7L–&#8377;9L/month.</p>
                                        <h3>Do Kolkata studios handle DPDP / India data residency?</h3>
                                        <p>Yes — most Tier-1 Kolkata studios deploy on AWS Mumbai / Hyderabad, are familiar with the DPDP Act 2023, and ship apps with data-residency by default. Confirm in the contract.</p>
                                        <h3>How fast can we start?</h3>
                                        <p>Discovery + scoping inside week 1. Sprint 1 kickoff in week 2. First demo in week 4. Most Kolkata studios can ramp a 4–6 person team within 2 weeks for new projects.</p>
